					Biographies





Name
Description




							Hassell McClellan


					
							Dr. Hassell H. McClellan serves as Chairman of the Board of Trustee of the Company. He was Independent Trustee of the Fund. Associate Professor, Dr. McClellan serve as a former professor of finance and policy in the graduate management department of a major university, a current director of a public company, and as a former director of several privately held companies, Mr. McClellan has experience in corporate and financial matters. He also has experience as a director of other investment companies not affiliated with the Trust.




							Andrew Arnott


					
							Mr. Andrew G. Arnott is President of John Hancock Preferred Income Fund. He serves as Senior Vice President of John Hancock Financial Services (since 2009); Director and Executive Vice President of John Hancock Advisers, LLC (since 2005, including prior positions); Director and Executive Vice President of John Hancock Investment Management Services, LLC (since 2006, including prior positions); President of John Hancock Funds, LLC (since 2004, including prior positions); President of John Hancock retail funds and John Hancock Variable Insurance Trust and John Hancock Funds II (since 2007, including prior positions); President of John Hancock Collateral Trust (since 2015); President of John Hancock Exchange-Traded Fund Trust (since 2014).




							Steven Pruchansky


					
							Mr. Steven R. Pruchansky is Independent Vice Chairman of the Board of Trustees of the Fund. Mr. Pruchansky serves as Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Greenscapes of Southwest Florida, Inc. (since 2000); Director and President of Greenscapes of Southwest Florida, Inc. (until 2000); Member of Board of Advisors in First American Bank (until 2010); Managing Director of Jon James, LLC (real estate) (since 2000); Partner of Right Funding, LLC (since 2014); Director of First Signature Bank & Trust Company (until 1991); Director of Mast Realty Trust (until 1994); President of Maxwell Building Corp. (until 1991). Trustee (since 1992) and Chairperson of the Board (2011-2012), John Hancock retail funds; Trustee and Vice Chairperson of the Board of John Hancock retail funds and John Hancock Variable Insurance Trust and John Hancock Funds II (since 2012); Trustee and Vice Chairperson of the Board of John Hancock Collateral Trust and John Hancock Exchange-Traded Fund Trust (since 2015).




							Charles Rizzo


					
							Mr. Charles A. Rizzo is Chief Financial Officer of John Hancock Preferred Income Fund, since 2007. He is Vice President of John Hancock Financial Services (since 2008); Senior Vice President of John Hancock Advisers, LLC and John Hancock Investment Management Services, LLC (since 2008); Chief Financial Officer of John Hancock retail funds, John Hancock Variable Insurance Trust and John Hancock Funds II (since 2007); Chief Financial Officer of John Hancock Collateral Trust and John Hancock Exchange-Traded Fund Trust (since 2015).




							John Danello


					
							Mr. John J. Danello is Senior Vice President, Secretary and Chief Legal Officer of the Company. Mr. Danello serves as a Vice President and Chief Counsel of John Hancock Wealth Management (since 2005); Senior Vice President (since 2007) and Chief Legal Counsel (2007-2010), John Hancock Funds, LLC and The Berkeley Financial Group, LLC; Senior Vice President (since 2006, including prior positions) and Chief Legal Officer and Secretary (since 2014), John Hancock retail funds, John Hancock Funds II and John Hancock Variable Insurance Trust; Senior Vice President, Chief Legal Officer and Secretary (since 2015), John Hancock Collateral Trust; Vice President of John Hancock Life & Health Insurance Company (since 2009); Vice President of John Hancock Life Insurance Company (USA) and John Hancock Life Insurance Company of New York (since 2010); and Senior Vice President, Secretary, and Chief Legal Counsel (2007-2014, including prior positions) of John Hancock Advisers, LLC and John Hancock Investment Management Services, LLC; Senior Vice President, Secretary and Chief Legal Officer, John Hancock Exchange-Traded Fund Trust (since 2015).




							Francis Knox


					
							Mr. Francis V. Knox, Jr., is Chief Compliance Officer of John Hancock Preferred Income Fund, since 2005. He is Vice President of John Hancock Financial Services (since 2005); Chief Compliance Officer of John Hancock retail funds, John Hancock Variable Insurance Trust, John Hancock Funds II, John Hancock Advisers, LLC, and John Hancock Investment Management Services, LLC (since 2005)




							Salvatore Schiavone


					
							Mr. Salvatore Schiavone is Treasurer of John Hancock Preferred Income Fund, since 2009. He is Assistant Vice President of John Hancock Financial Services (since 2007); Vice President of John Hancock Advisers, LLC and John Hancock Investment Management Services, LLC (since 2007); Treasurer of John Hancock retail funds (since 2007, including prior positions); Treasurer of John Hancock Variable Insurance Trust and John Hancock Funds II (2007–2009 and since 2010, including prior positions).




							Charles Bardelis


					
							Mr. Charles L. Bardelis is an Independent Trustee of the Fund. As a Director of Island Commuter Corp. (marine transport). Trustee of John Hancock Collateral Trust and John Hancock Exchange-Traded Fund Trust (since 2015); Trustee of John Hancock retail funds (since 2012); Trustee of John Hancock Funds III (2005-2006 and since 2012); Trustee of John Hancock Variable Insurance Trust (since 1988); Trustee of John Hancock Funds II (since 2005).




							James Boyle


					
							Mr. James R. Boyle is Non-Independent Trustee of John Hancock Preferred Income Fund. Mr. Boyle served as a chairman and director of the Advisor, position as a senior executive of Manulife Financial Corporation (MFC), the Advisor's parent company, and positions with other affiliates of the Advisor, Mr. Boyle has experience in the development and management of registered investment companies, variable annuities and retirement products, enabling him to provide management input to the Board. He also has experience as a senior executive of healthcare and insurance companies.




							Craig Bromley


					
							Mr. Craig Bromley is Non-Independent Trustee of the Fund. Through his positions as President and Chief Executive Officer of Manulife Life Insurance Company (Manulife Japan), positions as a senior executive of MFC, the Advisor's parent company, and positions with other affiliates of the Advisor, Mr. Bromley has experience as a strategic business builder, expanding product offerings and distribution, enabling him to provide valuable management input to the Board.




							Peter Burgess


					
							Mr. Peter S. Burgess is an Independent Trustee of the Fund. Mr. Burgess serve as a financial consultant, certified public accountant and a former partner in a major international public accounting firm, Mr. Burgess has experience in the auditing of financial services companies and mutual funds. He also has experience as a director of publicly traded operating companies.




							William Cunningham


					
							Dr. William H. Cunningham, Ph.D., is Independent Trustee of John Hancock Preferred Income Fund, since 2002. Mr. Cunningham has management and operational oversight experience as a former Chancellor and President of a major university. Mr. Cunningham regularly teaches a graduate course in corporate governance at the law school and at the Red McCombs School of Business at The University of Texas at Austin. He also has oversight and corporate governance experience as a current and former director of a number of operating companies, including an insurance company.




							Grace Fey


					
							Ms. Grace K. Fey is an independent Trustee of the Fund. She has been consultant to nonprofit and corporate boards, and as a former director and executive of an investment management firm, Ms. Fey has experience in the investment management industry. She also has experience as a director of an operating company.




							Theron Hoffman


					
							Mr. Theron S. Hoffman is an Independent Trustee of the Fund. He serves as a consultant and as a former senior executive and director of several large public and private companies, including a global reinsurance company and a large investment management firm, Mr. Hoffman has extensive experience in corporate governance, business operations and new product development. In addition, his prior service as chair of corporate pension trusts has given him experience in the oversight of investment managers.




							Deborah Jackson


					
							Ms. Deborah C. Jackson is Independent Trustee of John Hancock Preferred Income Fund, since 2008. Ms. Jackson has management and operational oversight experience as the president of a college and as the former chief executive officer of a major charitable organization. She also has oversight and corporate governance experience as a current and former director of various corporate organizations, including a bank, an insurance company, a regional stock exchange and nonprofit entities.




							James Oates


					
							Mr. James M. Oates serves as Trustee of the Company. He was Independent Chairman of the Board of Trustees of the Fund. He serves as Managing Director, Wydown Group (financial consulting firm) (since 1994); Chairman and Director of Emerson Investment Management, Inc. (since 2000); Independent Chairman of Hudson Castle Group, Inc. (formerly IBEX Capital Markets, Inc.) (financial services company) (1997–2011); Director of Stifel Financial (since 1996); Director of Investor Financial Services Corporation (1995–2007); Director of Connecticut River Bancorp (1998-2014); Director of Virtus Funds (formerly Phoenix Mutual Funds) (since 1988). Trustee and Chairperson of the Board, John Hancock Collateral Trust and John Hancock Exchange-Traded Fund Trust (since 2015); Trustee and Chairperson of the Board, John Hancock retail funds (since 2012); Trustee (2005-2006 and since 2012) and Chairperson of the Board (since 2012), John Hancock Funds III; Trustee (since 2004) and Chairperson of the Board (since 2005), John Hancock Variable Insurance Trust; Trustee and Chairperson of the Board, John Hancock Funds II (since 2005).




							Gregory Russo


					
							Mr. Gregory A. Russo is an Independent Trustee of John Hancock Preferred Income Fund, since 2008. He is certified public accountant and former partner in a major independent registered public accounting firm, Mr. Russo has accounting and executive experience. He also has experience as a current and former director of various operating entities.




							Warren Thomson


					
							Mr. Warren A. Thomson is Non-Independent Trustee of the Fund. He served as a Chairman of Manulife Asset Management and Chief Investment Officer of MFC, the Advisor's parent company, Mr. Thomson has experience in the management of investments, registered investment companies, variable annuities and retirement products, enabling him to provide management input to the Board.











